{{Infobox person |name = Antoine Alphonse Chassepot |image = Antoine Alphonse Chassepot.png |image_size = |alt = |caption = Antoine Alphonse Chassepot |birth_name = Antoine Alphonse Chassepot |birth_date = {{Birth date|1833|03|04}} |birth_place = [[Mutzig]], [[France]] |death_date = {{Death date and age|1905|02|05|1833|03|04}} |death_place =[[Alsace]] |employer = |occupation = inventor |spouse= |children = }} [[File:Chassepot-p1000738.jpg|thumb|A [[Chassepot]].]] '''Antoine Alphonse Chassepot''' (1833–1905) was a [[France|French]] inventor and gunsmith. He was born in 1833 at [[Mutzig]] in Alsace. He invented the [[breech-loading]], center-fire [[needle gun]] rifle known as the [[Chassepot]]. It was adopted by the French army in 1866 for which he received the [[Légion d'honneur|Cross of the Légion d'honneur]] and a gratuity of 30,000 [[franc]]s.<ref>{{cite book|title =Rifles of the World|page=86|author =John Walter |edition =3|publisher =Krause Publications|year= 2006 |location=Iola| ISBN = 978-0-89689-241-5 }}</ref>
