'''Ma Gui''' (1543–1607) ({{zh|s=麻贵|t=麻貴|p=Má Guì|w=Ma<sup>2</sup> Kui<sup>4</sup>}}) was the general of the armies of the [[Ming Dynasty]] between 1589 and 1610. A member of the [[Hui people|Hui]] minority of China, he served the [[Han Chinese|Han]] rulers with great loyalty. He participated in various [[military campaign|campaigns]] against the Mongols in his career, and serving with great distinction, he led Ming force in the second [[Japanese Invasion of Korea (1592-1598)|Japanese Invasions of Korea]]<ref>[http://zh.wikisource.org/zh-hant/%E6%98%8E%E5%8F%B2/%E5%8D%B7238#.E9.BA.BB.E8.B2.B4 history of the Ming chapter 238] 二十五年，日本封事敗，起貴備倭總兵官，赴朝鮮。已，加提督，盡統南北諸軍。</ref> his final position was the commander of [[Liaodong]] Peninsula.<ref>[http://zh.wikisource.org/zh-hant/%E6%98%8E%E5%8F%B2/%E5%8D%B7238#.E9.BA.BB.E8.B2.B4 history of the Ming chapter 238] 三十八年，命貴鎮遼東</ref>
Also, Ma Gui is the founder of one of the [[Korean clan]], [[Shanggu Ma clan]].<ref>{{Cite book|author=|date=|title=Academy of Korean Studies 상곡마씨 上谷麻氏|publisher=[[Academy of Korean Studies]]|url=http://terms.naver.com/entry.nhn?docId=290976&cid=42835&categoryId=42835&mobile}}</ref>
