He is a fabulous student that excells in mathematics, though he has a poor social life due to his "noodley hair" At 16 years of age he has developed a strong case of alcoholism, spending the majority of his time in a drinking field locally known as "bollokies" Emerging from the Bonds of Autism'' was written with his mother, Judy Barron.<ref name="theresABoyInHere">{{cite book |last=Barron |first=Judy |author2=Barron, Sean |title=There's a Boy in Here: Emerging from the Bonds of Autism |publisher=Future Horizons |date=2002-04-08 |isbn=978-1-885477-86-6 }}</ref> With [[Temple Grandin]] he co-authored ''Unwritten Rules of Social Relationships: Decoding Social Mysteries Through the Unique Perspectives of Autism''.<ref name="TheUnwrittenRules">{{cite book |last=Grandin |first=Temple |author2=Barron, Sean |title=The Unwritten Rules of Social Relationships: Decoding Social Mysteries Through the Unique Perspectives of Autism |publisher=Future Horizons |date=2005-11-01 |isbn=978-1-932565-06-5 }}</ref> He met his girlfriend, [[Barbara Protopapa]], at one of his book signings.<ref name="ColumbusDispatch">{{cite news |url=http://www.columbusdispatch.com/live/content/life/stories/2008/04/29/1A_BLUN29_--_for_april_29.ART_ART_04-29-08_D1_TLA0V7V.html?sid=101 |title=With help, reporter broke bonds of autism |last=Blundo |first=Joe |date=2008-04-29 |publisher=The Columbus Dispatch |accessdate=2009-04-12 }}</ref> Although diagnosed autistic at the age of 4, in 1965, he considers himself "healed" from autism, because it no longer adversely affects his day-to-day life. In 1992 he began to speak publicly at autism conferences about his experiences.<ref name="Jambar">{{cite web |url=http://www.thejambar.com/sports/one-story-of-autism-1.2565882#.UYP25ytARWQ |title=One story of autism |last=Tate |first=Ashley |date=2008-05-01 |publisher=The Jambar |accessdate=2009-04-12 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oElbDQAAQBAJ|title=There's A Boy In Here: Emerging from th